{"builtWith":"0.15.15","comments":[{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":"                                               // hydrogen // matroid // class"},{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":" | Matroid Typeclass"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | A matroid M = (E, I) is a combinatorial structure where:"},{"LineComment":" | - E is a finite ground set"},{"LineComment":" | - I ⊆ 2^E is a family of \"independent\" sets"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Matroid Axioms:"},{"LineComment":" | 1. ∅ ∈ I (empty set is independent)"},{"LineComment":" | 2. If A ∈ I and B ⊆ A, then B ∈ I (hereditary property)"},{"LineComment":" | 3. If A, B ∈ I and |A| < |B|, then ∃x ∈ B\\A such that A ∪ {x} ∈ I (exchange)"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Why Matroids Matter"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Greedy maximization of a monotone submodular function subject to a matroid"},{"LineComment":" | constraint achieves (1 - 1/e) ≈ 0.632 approximation. This is optimal for"},{"LineComment":" | polynomial-time algorithms."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Common Matroids"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | - **Cardinality**: I = {S : |S| ≤ k}"},{"LineComment":" | - **Partition**: Ground set partitioned, at most k_i from each partition"},{"LineComment":" | - **Uniform**: Any k elements can be chosen"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | For render quality allocation, we use a **partition matroid** over render"},{"LineComment":" | tiers (foveal/peripheral/background) with tier-specific bounds."}],"decls":[{"annotation":{"meta":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[0,0],"start":[0,0]}},"bindType":"NonRec","expression":{"abstraction":{"annotation":{"meta":{"metaType":"IsForeign"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[154,8],"start":[154,3]}},"type":"Var","value":{"identifier":"foldl","moduleName":["Data","Foldable"]}},"annota